intro: Oenanthe australiana, commonly known as the Australian cow-weed, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the Apiaceae family, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided, fern-like leaves. The plant produces small, white or pale green flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the family. It is often found in coastal areas and sandy soils, thriving in well-drained conditions. Oenanthe australiana is an important plant in ecological studies due to its role in supporting local insect populations.
